entries.content: NDESOR authors decided to remove Sweet Lorraine (DE6539b), because a non-Ellington item, Correction Sheet 5005. Ben Young in the liner notes of Bb 09026-63953-2 explains: «The Pittsburgh Piano Workshop was so spontaneous that Billy Taylor's announcement of a Hines-Ellington duet was followed instead by Sweet Lorraine, a Taylor and Hines duet. The location engineers were confused and left Ellington's name alongside Sweet Lorraine on the tape box, which explains why this item was long thought to include all three pianists.»
